view.name: Electric Vehicle Population Size History By County
view.description:
This shows the number of vehicles that were registered by Washington State Department of Licensing (DOL) each month. The data is separated by county for passenger vehicles and trucks. 

DOL integrates National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) data and the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) fuel efficiency ratings with DOL titling and registration data to create this information.

columns.name: Date
columns.description: Counts of registered vehicles are taken on this day (the end of this month).

columns.name: County
columns.description: This is the geographic region of a state that a vehicle's owner is listed to reside within. Vehicles registered in Washington state may be located in other states.

columns.name: State
columns.description: This is the geographic region of the country associated with the record. These addresses may be located in other states.

columns.name: Vehicle Primary Use
columns.description: This describes the primary intended use of the vehicle.

columns.name: Battery Electric Vehicles (BEVs)
columns.description: The count of vehicles that are known to be propelled solely by an energy derived from an onboard electric battery.

columns.name: Plug-In Hybrid Electric Vehicles (PHEVs)
columns.description: The count of vehicles that are known to be propelled from energy partially sourced from an onboard electric battery that is capable of being recharged from an external source.

columns.name: Electric Vehicle (EV) Total
columns.description: The sum of Battery Electric Vehicles (BEVs) and Plug-in Hybrid Electric Vehicles (PHEVs).

columns.name: Non-Electric Vehicle Total
columns.description: The count of vehicles that are not electric vehicles.

columns.name: Total Vehicles
columns.description: All powered vehicles registered in the county. This includes electric vehicles.

columns.name: Percent Electric Vehicles
columns.description: Comparison of electric vehicles versus their non-electric counterparts.

license.name: Open Data Commons Open Database License

Temporal.Period of Time: Data includes historical Electric Vehicle population counts from January 2017 through February 2025.

Identification.Originator: Research and Analysis Office, Department of Licensing

A Battery Electric Vehicle (BEV) is an all-electric vehicle using one or more batteries to store the electrical energy that powers the motor and is charged by plugging the vehicle in to an electric power source. A Plug-in Hybrid Electric Vehicle (PHEV) is a vehicle that uses one or more batteries to power an electric motor; uses another fuel, such as gasoline or diesel, to power an internal combustion engine or other propulsion source; and is charged by plugging the vehicle in to an electric power source.
Vehicles registered with a military installation address may not have an assigned county. These vehicles are not included in the final counts.
Monthly count of vehicles for a county may change from this report and prior reports. Processes were implemented to more accurately assign county at the time of registration.
